Equity Commentary
U.S. equity markets continued their gains during the second quarter of 2017 with the S&P 500 up 3.09%, lifting returns to 9.34% year to date.
Read more »



 









Alternative Investment Commentary
Hedge funds extended their trend in the second quarter of 2017 as the HFRI Fund-of-Funds Composite Index rose by 0.2%.
Read more »



 









Fixed Income Commentary
The Fed struck again and raised rates 25 basis points at its June meeting, with the potential for another rate increase in the second half of 2017.
Read more »



 






Q1 | 2017



Fixed Income Commentary
The Fed hiked rates at its March meeting, but the pace of future rate increases will be dependent on economic data and fiscal policy going forward. The FOMC voted to raise the target range of the federal funds rate to between .75%and 1.00% on March 15th.
